Data standardization

Source: R/standardize.R
standardize.Rd

Perform data standardization for multivariate exploratory data analysis.

Usage

standardize(X, type = c("FactoMineR", "norm"), ...)

Arguments

X

matrix

type

nature of standardization

...

additional arguments

Details

Standardization depends on what you need to perform factor analysis. Actually, there are only two types:

  • type = "FactoMineR": standardization is performed by centering the data matrix and dividing by the square root of the sum of squares of the weights. This is the default standardization in FactoMineR::PCA(..., scale.unit = TRUE).

  • type = "norm": standardization is performed by centering and scaling the data matrix. This is the default standardization in R.

Examples

library(FactoMineR2)

iris[, -5] |>
  standardize(type = "norm")
